This paper deals with the problem of detecting vandalism in Wikipedia, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves feature extraction and supervised learning algorithms, which are common in Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the problem of detecting vandalism can be seen as a security issue, which falls under the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves the use of algorithms to automatically detect patterns in data, which is a common theme in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
